7/ Thanks for bearing with us. Please accept our apology and thank you for your patience as we work through this. We know this isn't ideal and its not how we wanted it to go up until now but we are very close and will keep you all plugged in throughout the process!

6/ We left a large buffer window but Pi√±ata (the IPFS pinning service). Although we verified with them several times throughout the week and ran dummy tests, their service is not accepting our overall file size. No one from their team is available.

5/ The reason this is something that we are only dealing with now is because we wanted to prevent anyone sniping or having unfair advantages on secondary. We didn't want to run the risk of leaving the images/metadata floating around somewhere.
3/ Instead of lowering image quality and patching the situation, we‚Äôve chosen to delay our reveal by approximately 2 hours.

2/ Our images and metadata were fully uploaded to IPFS, but due to the large size of our 2K image files, they're just loading too slowly and we're worried that OpenSea will take too long to pull the images and it will lead to a drawn out reveal process.

1/ ANTONYM REVEAL DELAY - 2 HOURS
